      <div class="msgContentFrame">I can't confirm anything as I am not the testing type but I can tell you how I do things.  I am primarly a Gladiator (13) with pugilist (9), conjurer (8), and thaumaturge (6) for the extra abilities. My stats are str, vit, dex at 40 int and piety at 20 and mnd at 22.  I can tank any solo mob orange and below easily, I am in LL so group mobs there are the giant crabs of pain.  Those I need a group with.  I am sitting at just over 900 hp including gear bonuses but respect some points into vit when grouping with crabs. <br /> <br />My suggestion for if you want to tank in a party primarily is to keep that VIT up high, and alos MND if you are planning on curing yourself.  However if you do this use really need to adept at keeping your shield up and getting phalanx in whenever possible.  Another ability that may help is Haymaker from Pugilist. That you receive at rank 4 and allows you to counter attack when you evade an enemy hit.  This way you have two low cost TP abilities (250) to generate hate with while keeping your defense up.  One last suggestion would be level pugilist to 10 so you can have a second provoke handy. <br /> <br />Hope that is helpful.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Squire Kalyista Ayanna, Spell Sword <br />Besaid <br /> <br />Lady Kalista Elandrastaar, Mage Knight <br />(62 RDM - Valefor)</div></div>
