      <div class="msgContentFrame">Just my persona pov <br /> <br />Having any points in mind is usless, because all you need is to get a Thauturmage to rank 16 to get Stygian Spikes. <br />Stygian Spikes recover your mp when you get hit, which you obviously will be as a tank. <br /> <br />And I wouldn't ignore Str either, at low lvls it might seem ok to go full vit, but you won't be lvling fast to begin with, let alone doing low dmg.  <br />Every enemy out there is capped to give a max of 500SP. For gladiator both shield and sword SP fall under the same 500SP cap, so even if you get 400shield and 300 sword SP it will be something like 235shield 265sword. <br />You honestly don't need too high of a vit (especially since there is a rank/plvl cap for each stat) and getting more SP per hit (because of the higher dmg) is just that little bit that ll make the already hard later on gladi lvling more durable.</div>
