      <div class="msgContentFrame">Go play with some Imps and you will notice the difference MND makes when you, and the healer are the only ones left standing after the fun AOEs they throw around. AOE Blizzard II is fun. <br />VIT isn't as broken as it was in FFXI - adding VIT lessens damage inflicted.. or so I have seen so far. <br />I keep VIT at cap for my level, then have DEX and STR at a reasonable level and MND up. My physical level (35) far surpasses my gladiator level (20) due to crafting, so it's probably cap for those 4 at this point.  <br /> <br />I haven't noticed increased damage = increased SP.. but I haven't payed attention. That also doesn't make sense to me, as lower level mobs would give more SP because you can whack the [expletive] out of them.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>FFXI: Rison of Alexander (retired) <br />FFXIV: Rison Srithuram of Palamecia <br />LS: Omnipresence [ <a href="http://omnipresencels.com" title="http://omnipresencels.com" rel="external nofollow">http://omnipresencels.com</a> ]</div></div>
