      <div class="msgContentFrame">The fact it doesn't make sense to you doesn't change the way the game is made. <br />Imps using their aoe don't kill me either, (not just imps, but the devilets upgraded version of imps from rank 30 leves aswell) and I have no mind points added at all, with pretty low vit for my lvl. <br />I restatted from capped vit to capped str, before, and been taking same physical dmg from the same mobs at that same lvl, with a lot less vit. <br /> <br />All with all since stat points start to cost 3 after 80, I ll be getting my str and vit to 80, while leaving dex at 60, before I continue on with my str.  <br /> <br />As for the dmg per hit giving more SP per hit, every difficulty of monster has a chance of giving a certain ammount of SP it gives per dmg done. Now if you go hit low lvl mobs, if you hit it for 50 it ll give you 10sp, if you hit it for 100 it ll give you 20sp or so. Do that on a high lvl mob 50 dmg ll give you 75sp 100dmg ll give you 150sp, just random numbers but more dmg still earns you more SP. <br /> <br />But you really should try restatting, before keeping stats for what they don't do.</div>
